Description: Fragment of wall of North Ionian pottery plate or dish; cream slip. Underside reserved with single orange-fired band; on floor, frieze of dots outside frieze of leaves and buds, similarly fired. Graffito on underside.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (Rhodian 173)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.518)
